-- Mursi Says Truce Bid to Show Results in Hours, Mena Reports
-- B y   S a l m a   E l   W a r d a n y
-- 2012-11-20T13:51:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-20/mursi-says-truce-bid-to-show-results-in-hours-mena-reports-1-.html
Egyptian President Mohamed Mursi
said today that efforts to achieve a truce between Israel and
Hamas will yield positive results within the next few hours, the
state-run Middle East  News Agency  reported.  Mursi said that the Israeli “aggression” on Gaza will end
today, MENA and state-run Nile News reported, citing the
president’s comments at his sister’s funeral.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Salma El Wardany in Cairo at 
 selwardany@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  